  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> </strong>and cut in half using a sharp knife</p><p>Tip: Drizzle the knife with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> for easier chopping</p><p>Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634039907051-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634039907051-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634039907051-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634039907051-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1634039907051-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut narrow slices (about 1cm in width) into the <strong>butternut squash halves</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base – this is your<strong> hasselback butternut squash</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>hasselback butternut squash </strong>to a baking tray, cut side up and drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 30 min or until the squash is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1634039918982-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1634039918982-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1634039918982-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1634039918982-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1634039918982-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grate the<strong> cheddar cheese</strong> into a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and season with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cheesy breadcrumb mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634039925428-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634039925428-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634039925428-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634039925428-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1634039925428-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add to a tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the potatoes are crisp – these are your <strong>roast potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1634039929348-x200.jpg",
